==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[comprehendere]]'', "to [[grasp]]", from the prefix ''[[com-]]'', + ''[[prehendere]]'', "to seize".

===Verb===
'''to comprehend'''
# to [[cover]], [[include]], or [[contain]]
#:''This book '''comprehends''' all the topics that are relevant for you.''
# to [[understand]] or [[grasp]] [[fully]] and [[thorough]]ly.
